•	Prerequisites
Before running the test, ensure your system meets the following requirements:
🧰 Software Requirements
1.	Java JDK 11 or higher
o	Download JDK
2.	Google Chrome (latest version)
3.	ChromeDriver
o	Download from: https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads
4.	TestNG (if using Eclipse)
o	Open Eclipse → Help → Eclipse Marketplace → search TestNG → install.
5.	Apache POI JARs (for Excel handling)
If not using Maven, download manually from https://poi.apache.org/download.html.

•	Project Structure
├── src
│   ├── main/java/assesment/Brainholic_/enrichminion_test.java
│   └── test/java/tests/
│       ├── TC_01_login.java
│       ├── TC_02_xllogin.java
├── testdata/
│   ├── loginData.xlsx
│   └── loginReport.xlsx (auto-created)
├── testng.xml
├── pom.xml (if Maven project)
└── README.md


•	Running the Selenium Tests
 Option 1: Run from Eclipse / IntelliJ
Step-by-step:
1.	Open Eclipse or IntelliJ IDEA.
2.	Import the project as a Java Project or Maven Project.
3.	Make sure your ChromeDriver path is configured properly.
4.	Open the class you want to run:
o	TC_01_login.java or
o	TC_02_xllogin.java
5.	Right-click inside the file → Run As → TestNG Test
TestNG will open Chrome, execute steps, and generate a report in the console (and Excel file if applicable).
 Option 2: Run via Command Prompt (CMD)
 Step 1 — Navigate to Project Directory
Code:

cd path\to\your\project

 Step 2 — Compile Java Files
If you’re not using Maven:

javac -cp "lib/*;src" src\assesment\Brainholic_\enrichminion_test.java

If using Maven:

mvn clean compile

 Step 3 — Run Specific Test via TestNG XML
To run TC_01_login:


mvn test -DsuiteXmlFile=testng_TC01.xml

To run TC_02_xllogin:

mvn test -DsuiteXmlFile=testng_TC02.xml
•	Viewing the Output
For TC_02_xllogin, output file:

testdata/loginReport.xlsx

